article.headline: Alcorn State 84, Texas Southern 77
article.story: LORMAN, Miss. (AP) -- Carl Landry scored eight of his 19 points down the stretch, and Alcorn State clinched a berth in the Southwestern Athletic Conference tournament with an 84-77 win over Texas Southern on Thursday night. Texas Southern closed to 66-64 on a free throw by Jacques Jones with 6:37 left. That's when Landry took over, hitting a jumper, converting a three-point play and hit a 15-footer to push the Braves' lead to 75-68. Alcorn State then made 7-of-10 free throws in the final minute to seal the victory. Alcorn State (7-19, 7-10) clinched a spot in next week's eight-team tournament in Birmingham, Ala., with the win and Arkansas-Pine Bluff's victory over Mississippi Valley State, school officials said. Delvin Thompson had 15 points, and James Kendrick and Clif Douglass added 10 apiece for Alcorn State, which committed a season-low 10 turnovers and outrebounded Texas Southern 38-34. Jones had 18 points and 11 rebounds to lead Texas Southern (8-21, 6-11).
